{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775873492460,"sessionID":"ses_285b351c9ffeisKLz4DZy8C60B","part":{"id":"prt_d7a4cc3da001cuPV2r3XVYMR7I","messageID":"msg_d7a4caf240012YCsKstddnzh84","sessionID":"ses_285b351c9ffeisKLz4DZy8C60B","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_3ad018d1eddf49cab5c09799","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project structure thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project directory structure\n2. What's in the `manifests/` directory (if it exists)\n3. Any existing RBAC-related files (ClusterRole, Role, ClusterRoleBinding, RoleBinding, ServiceAccount)\n4. Any existing tasks.md or similar checklist files for reference on format\n5. Any design documents related to ST-3 or AR-031\n6. The project's conventions for YAML manifests (naming, labels, annotations)\n\nSearch broadly across the project. Return:\n- Full directory tree (relevant parts)\n- Contents of any existing RBAC manifests\n- Contents of any existing tasks.md files for format reference\n- Any design spec files related to this work\n- Naming conventions and patterns used in the project","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_285b3238fffe2xESzoIGpnTsG8 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is the complete report:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Project Directory Structure\n\nThe workspace at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z` contains the AgentCube project with the following top-level structure:\n\n```\nagentcube/\n├── changes/                          # Architecture Records (AR-001 through AR-031)\n│   ├── AR-001/ ... AR-031/           # Each contains: proposal.md, design.md, delta-spec.md, tasks.md\n├── cmd/                              # Go binaries (agentd, cli, picod, router, workloadmanager)\n├── pkg/                              # Go packages (agentd, apis, common, picod, store, etc.)\n├── manifests/                        # Helm chart for Kubernetes deployment\n│   └── charts/\n│       └── base/\n│           ├── Chart.yaml\n│           ├── values.yaml\n│           ├── crds/\n│           │   ├── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n│           │   └── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\n│           └── templates/\n│               ├── _helpers.tpl\n│               ├── workloadmanager.yaml          # WM Deployment + Service\n│               ├── agentcube-router.yaml          # Router Deployment + Service\n│               ├── rbac-router.yaml               # Router RBAC (SA + Role + RoleBinding)\n│               ├── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml  # Volcano (mixed RBAC + non-RBAC)\n│               └── rbac/\n│                   └── workloadmanager.yaml       # WM RBAC (SA + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding)\n├── deployment/                       # Deployment design docs (design.md, spec.md, etc.)\n├── ci-cd/                            # CI/CD design docs\n├── cli-toolkit/                      # CLI toolkit design docs\n├── code-execution/                   # Code execution design docs\n├── idle-cleanup/                     # Idle cleanup design docs\n├── integrations/                     # Integration design docs\n├── python-sdk/                       # Python SDK design docs\n├── sandbox-orchestration/            # Sandbox orchestration design docs\n├── session-routing/                  # Session routing design docs\n├── session-store/                    # Session store design docs\n├── client-go/                        # Go client design docs\n├── project.md                        # Project overview\n├── proposal.md                       # Top-level proposal\n├── tasks.md                          # Top-level tasks\n├── delta-spec.md                     # Top-level delta spec\n├── design.md                         # Top-level design\n├── test_spec.md                      # Test spec\n├── go.mod / go.sum                   # Go module files\n└── test/ / testing/                  # Test files\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Manifests Directory Contents\n\nFull path: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/manifests/charts/base/`\n\n```\nmanifests/charts/base/\n├── Chart.yaml            # apiVersion: v1, name: agentcube, version: 0.1.0, appVersion: 1.0.0\n├── values.yaml           # 65 lines - component configuration (redis, router, workloadmanager, volcano)\n├── crds/\n│   ├── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n│   └── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\n└── templates/\n    ├── _helpers.tpl                              # 45 lines - agentcube.name, agentcube.fullname, agentcube.chart, agentcube.labels, agentcube.selectorLabels\n    ├── workloadmanager.yaml                       # WM Deployment + Service (76 lines)\n    ├── agentcube-router.yaml                      # Router Deployment + Service (79 lines)\n    ├── rbac-router.yaml                           # Router RBAC: SA + Role + RoleBinding (42 lines, conditional)\n    ├── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml   # Volcano: SA + ConfigMap + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding + Service + Deployment (296 lines, conditional)\n    └── rbac/\n        └── workloadmanager.yaml                   # WM RBAC: SA + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding (149 lines, NO values gate)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing RBAC-Related Files\n\n### 3a. `templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` (149 lines)\n- **ServiceAccount**: `workloadmanager` (namespace-scoped)\n- **ClusterRole**: `workloadmanager` (cluster-scoped, no `agentcube-` prefix)\n- **ClusterRoleBinding**: `workloadmanager` (cluster-scoped)\n- **NO values gate** -- always rendered\n- **Labels**: Simple `app: workloadmanager` (NOT kubernetes standard labels)\n- Permissions cover: agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes, extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/*, runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/*, core pods/secrets, authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews\n\n### 3b. `templates/rbac-router.yaml` (42 lines)\n- **Gated by**: `{{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}`\n- **ServiceAccount**: `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}`\n- **Role**: Same name as SA (namespace-scoped)\n- **RoleBinding**: Same name as SA (namespace-scoped)\n- **Labels**: Simple `app: agentcube-router`\n- Permissions: core `secrets` full CRUD\n\n### 3c. `templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` (296 lines, RBAC portion)\n- **Gated by**: `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n- **ServiceAccount**: `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n- **ClusterRole**: `volcano-agent-scheduler` (no `agentcube-` prefix)\n- **ClusterRoleBinding**: `volcano-agent-scheduler-role`\n- **Labels**: Simple `app: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n- Mixed with non-RBAC resources: ConfigMap, Service, Deployment\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing tasks.md Files for Format Reference\n\n### Primary reference: `changes/AR-030/tasks.md` (322 lines) -- manifests module, YAML, Size L\n\n**Format pattern:**\n```markdown\n# AR-030 -- Helm Chart Templates and Values -- Tasks\n\n> **Module:** manifests\n> **Language:** YAML\n> **Size:** L\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-030/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-030/design.md`, `changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** `make gen-crd` available (or CRDs hand-written)\n\n---\n\n## T-001: Chart.yaml Metadata\n\n- [ ] T-001.01 Create directory `manifests/charts/base/`\n- [ ] T-001.02 Create `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml`\n- [ ] T-001.03 Set `apiVersion: v1`\n...\n\n**Verification**: `python3 -c \"import yaml; ...\"` no error\n\n---\n\n## Dependency Graph\n\n```\nT-001 --+-- T-002 --+-- T-005 --+\n        |           |-- T-006 --|-- T-011 (Lint + render)\n        |-- T-003 --|           |-- T-012 (Scenario tests)\n        |           |-- T-008 --|\n        |-- T-010 --+           |-- T-014 (dry-run)\n                                +-- T-015 (naming)\n```\n\n## Parallelizable Groups\n\n| Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n|-------|-------|---------------|\n| G1 | T-001, T-002 | None |\n| G2 | T-003, T-004 | G1 |\n...\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| # | Criterion | Command |\n|---|-----------|---------|\n| AC1 | Chart.yaml metadata correct | `python3 -c \"...\"` |\n| AC2 | values.yaml valid YAML | `python3 -c \"...\"` |\n...\n```\n\n### Secondary reference: `changes/AR-012/tasks.md` (146 lines) -- Go module, Size S\n\nUses the same format but with Go-specific verification commands (`go build`, `go test`, `go test -race`).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Design Documents Related to ST-3 and AR-031\n\n### AR-031 Files (all in `changes/AR-031/`):\n\n| File | Lines | Status |\n|------|-------|--------|\n| `proposal.md` | 116 | **COMPLETED** -- Full content with purpose, scope, architecture, impact analysis, alternatives |\n| `delta-spec.md` | 344 | **COMPLETED** -- 12 requirements, 35 GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios |\n| `design.md` | 689 | **COMPLETED** -- Full architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing strategy, implementation steps |\n| `tasks.md` | 25 | **EMPTY SCAFFOLD** -- Contains only TODO placeholders |\n\n### Key design decisions from AR-031:\n\n1. **Directory consolidation**: Move `rbac-router.yaml` to `rbac/router.yaml`; extract Volcano RBAC to `rbac/volcano-scheduler.yaml`\n2. **Naming convention**:\n   - ServiceAccount: `<component>` or `agentcube-<component>` (matches Deployment name)\n   - ClusterRole/Role: `agentcube-<component>` (add prefix to avoid cluster-wide conflicts)\n   - ClusterRoleBinding/RoleBinding: `agentcube-<component>-binding`\n3. **Labels**: All RBAC resources get `app.kubernetes.io/name`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance`, `app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac`\n4. **Values gates**:\n   - `workloadmanager.rbac.create: true` (new, default true for backward compat)\n   - `router.rbac.create: false` (existing, unchanged)\n   - `volcano.scheduler.rbac.create: \"\"` (new, empty string follows `enabled`)\n5. **_helpers.tpl**: Add `agentcube.rbacName` and `agentcube.rbacBindingName` helpers\n\n---\n\n## 6. Project Conventions for YAML Manifests\n\n### Naming conventions:\n- **Chart name**: `agentcube`\n- **Component names**: `workloadmanager`, `agentcube-router`, `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n- **RBAC files**: Currently inconsistent -- `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` vs `rbac-router.yaml` (flat). AR-031 proposes all under `rbac/` directory\n- **Template files**: `<component>.yaml` for Deployment+Service, `rbac/<component>.yaml` for RBAC\n\n### Label conventions (current):\n- Simple `app: <component-name>` labels used throughout\n- `_helpers.tpl` defines `agentcube.labels` and `agentcube.selectorLabels` with kubernetes standard labels, but these are NOT currently used in RBAC templates\n\n### Helm template conventions:\n- Namespace: `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n- Conditional rendering: `{{- if .Values.<component>.<flag> }}` / `{{- end }}`\n- Image: `\"{{ .Values.<component>.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.<component>.image.tag }}\"`\n- Multi-document separator: `---`\n- Values comments: YAML comments above each key describing purpose\n\n### tasks.md format conventions:\n- Header with Module, Language, Size, Precondition, Reference, Dependency\n- Tasks numbered `T-NNN` with sub-items `T-NNN.NN`\n- Each task group ends with `**Verification**:` line containing a shell command\n- Dependency graph in ASCII art\n- Parallelizable groups table\n- Acceptance criteria table with #, Criterion, Command columns\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_285b3238fffe2xESzoIGpnTsG8","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775873350765,"end":1775873492457}}}}
